# Rapha — Cursor AI Rules
# These rules apply to ALL edits in this project

## Identity
This is Rapha, an AI-powered mobile health app for Ethiopia built with Expo React Native and Supabase.

## Design System
- Colors: navy #0A1628 primary, teal #00C2A8 accent, #F8FAFC background
- All colors from src/theme.ts — never use hardcoded hex values in components
- Typography from src/theme.ts — never use hardcoded font sizes in components
- Border radius: sm=8, md=12, lg=16, xl=24
- Shadows: iOS shadowColor+shadowOffset, Android elevation

## Architecture Rules
- Edge functions: only change supabase/functions when the task explicitly asks for Dr Lucas, triage, OCR, search, or related backend fixes.
- Do not change src/lib/supabase.ts auth configuration unless the task says to.
- Route AI chat through supabase.functions.invoke('chat-triage') from the app client (implemented in src/lib/sessionStore.ts).
- Use useSafeAreaInsets for bottom padding on scroll views and fixed bottom bars; pair with SafeAreaView as needed.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states on every screen.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- Prefer async/await over long .then() chains
- useMemo/useCallback for expensive computations
- Always handle Supabase errors: const { data, error } = await supabase...
- Prefer StyleSheet.create; avoid inline style objects with more than two properties

## File Structure
- Screen files: app/(drawer)/[name].tsx
- Library files: src/lib/[name].ts
- Components: src/components/[Name].tsx
- Data: src/data/[name].ts

## Content Rules
- NO placeholder text — every user-visible string must be real product copy
- NO "coming soon" — build the flow or hide the entry point
- NO technical jargon visible to users (no "Supabase", "Edge Function", etc.)
- NO "MVP" in user-visible copy
- Disclaimer: Rapha helps you find care but does not replace a doctor

## Testing
- After substantive edits: npm run typecheck should pass
- Prefer testing on a device with Expo Go; watch keyboard overlap and bottom navigation overlap
